[*] Test: bare function refs inside conditionals

/Grant [R]: a role
	[!] — access granted for [R]

/Deny [R]: a role
	[!] — access denied for [R]

/Limit [R]: a role
	[!] — limited access for [R]

/CheckAccess
[R]: a role
	[1] — [R] == Admin ? Grant[ [R] ] | Deny[ [R] ]
	[^] WARNING: bare refs to Grant and Deny

	[2] — [R] == Admin ? /Grant[ [R] ] | /Deny[ [R] ]
	[^] OK: proper refs — no warnings

	[3] — [R] == Admin ? /Grant[ [R] ] | [R] == User ? Limit[ [R] ] | /Deny[ [R] ]
	[^] WARNING: bare ref to Limit only
